I have implemented a high-level C-Foreign Function Interface (CFFI),for =
Win/NT 4.0 x86, along the lines suggested by Huelsbergen's paper for =
SML/NJ. The OCAML version is a bit more flexible than the one currently =
in SML/NJ, but callback functions have not yet been implemented.

Check it out at

http://www.azstarnet.com/~dmcclain/cffi.zip

Huelsbergen's paper can be found at

